he number of shares outstanding by the stock's price. For companies with multiple common share classes, market capitalization includes both classes. Shares Outstanding Number of shares that are currently held by investors, including restricted shares owned by the company's officers and insiders as well as those held by the public. Public Float The number of shares in the hands of public investors and available to trade. To calculate, start with total shares outstanding and subtract the number of restricted shares. Restricted stock typically is that issued to company insiders with limits on when it may be traded. Dividend Yield A company's dividend expressed as a percentage of its current stock price.      Key Stock Data    P/E Ratio (TTM) N/A     EPS (TTM)  $-0.24      Market Cap $11.84 B     Shares Outstanding 973.08 M     Public Float 972.20 M     Yield 0.61% (07/21/17)      Latest Dividend $0.015 (06/30/17)      Ex-Dividend Date 06/13/17       ?    Shares Sold Short The total number of shares of a security that have been sold short and not yet repurchased. Change from Last Percentage change in short interest from the previous report to the most recent report. Exchanges report short interest twice a month. Percent of Float Total short positions relative to the number of shares available to trade.      Short Interest (06/30/17)    Shares Sold Short 13.83 M     Change from Last  -9.52%      Percent of Float 1.42%       ?    Money Flow Uptick/Downtick Ratio Money flow measures the relative buying and selling pressure on a stock, based on the value of trades made on an "uptick" in price and the value of trades made on a "downtick" in price. The up/down ratio is calculated by dividing the value of uptick trades by the value of downtick trades. Net money flow is the value of uptick trades minus the value of downtick trades. Our calculations are based on comprehensive, delayed quotes.      Stock Money Flow    Uptick/Downtick Trade Ratio  0 2    1.16      Net Money Flow ($)  6.11 M    Money flow gives a snapshot of relative buying and selling pressure in a stock. A ratio above one suggests greater buying pressure, below one suggests greater selling.               Advertisement         Competitors ECA      Company Change P/E (TTM)    CNQ Canadian Natural Resources Ltd.   -2.17% -0.66   239.13     HSE Husky Energy Inc.   -2.74% -0.40   10.11     SU Suncor Energy Inc.   -0.49% -0.15   33.67     DVN Devon Energy Corp.   -0.09% -0.03   57.90     MRO Marathon Oil Corp.   -2.07% -0.25   -     BT BT Group PLC ADR   -0.59% -0.12   16.07     ATH Athabasca Oil Corp.   -1.12% -0.01   -     VET Vermilion Energy Inc.   +0.35% +0.11   -        More information on ECA   Competitor Data Provided By: capital cube           Profile ECA      Encana Corp. operates as a natural gas company. It focuses on developing its portfolio of diverse resource plays producing natural gas, oil and natural gas liquids. The company operates through three segments: Canadian, the United States of America and Market Optimization....      500 Centre Street South East Calgary Alberta T2P 2S5 Canada   Email Website Map       Employees  2,200    Sector  Oil Extraction      Sales or Revenue  4.23 B    Industry  Companies on the Energy Service      1Y Sales Change  -13.66%    Fiscal Year Ends December 31 Download Reports          Douglas James Suttles President, Chief Executive Officer & Director       Michael G. McAllister Chief Operating Officer & Executive Vice President       Sherri A. Brillon Chief Financial Officer & Executive Vice President       David G. Hill Executive VP-Exploration & Business Development        More             Research & Ratings Encana Corp.ECA Per-Share Earnings, Actuals and Estimates      Quarterly   Annual    ECA will report FY 2017 earnings on 02/15/2018   ECA will report Q2 earnings on 07/21/2017         Actual     Analyst Range     Consensus      0.20  0.10  0.00  -0.10           -0.08        -0.02        0.02        0.03        0.03        0.0